main event: One object seen as a half circle, colored reddish and white, on 25 November 1956.
interesting points: The sighting was classified as incomplete with an unknown length of observation., The object was described as blinking and dividing into two., Various conclusions were drawn, including it possibly being a balloon or aircraft., A report was sent to acquire more information on 26 Nov 1956., The case was listed as having insufficient data for evaluation.
sighted object: one reddish and white half circle object
